body.p: STATE OF WASHINGTON COUNTY OF KING SS

Samuel H. Weber being first duly sworn on oath, deposes and says; That he is one of the signers of the bond in the case of the alien L. Orloff, that he resides at 1509 E. Spruce St. in the coty of Seattle, Washington, and that the value of his property over and above all debts and liabilities incurred by him and exclusive of propertyy exempt from levy and sale upon execution is over Two Thousand dollars ($2000.00)- to wit Real Estate in the City of Seattle, to the One Hundred and Twenty (120) feet of the South Sixty (60) feed of the North ONe Hundred and twenty (120) ett of the Tract 39 of esler's Donation Claim to the Cicty of Seattle, and that the present fair value of Depolots at 119-121 60th Street and the present fair value of Deponennt's interest is One Thousand Dollars ($1000.0 ); and personal property consisting of a ladies tailoring establishment at 406 Union St., Seattle Washington, consisting of Fixtures in the value of over $1000.00, and
